			<description><![CDATA[<p>
This position is for a contractor to be a key contributor for a series of on-going projects, part-time or full-time and 100% telecommuting is okay. Pingv has an immediate opening for an experienced Drupal Front-End Developer (FED) with a proven track record demonstrating mastery of architecture, design and code at the Drupal front-end. The FED will apply user-centric design methods to create functional, elegant Drupal sites and applications for Pingv&#39;s enterprise-level clients.</p>
<p>
We are looking for that smart, self-directed person with the right mix of passion for using Drupal-focused technology to solve problems, hands-on coding, mentoring others, talking to users, and contributing back to the open source community.</p>
<p>
At Pingv, we are building a great company filled with exceptional people who challenge and respect each other. Is this you?</p>
<p>
<strong>What You&#39;ll Do</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Lead front-end development for a variety of client projects.</li>
<li>
Custom Drupal theme development, following best practices in CSS/CSS3, HTML5/xhtml, jQuery, custom JavaScript, and Drupal API usage.</li>
<li>
Develop and iterate on design prototypes.</li>
<li>
Mentor and collaborate with colleagues and staff on best-in-class usability concepts.</li>
<li>
Participate and engage with the Drupal and front-end development communities.</li>
<li>
Collaborate with Pingv team designers, developers and managers.</li>
<li>
Drupal site-building and configuration as needed.</li>
<li>
Collaborate with designer and creative director in managing UX documents, such as user profiles, user stories, process flows, wireframes and user experience specifications.</li>
<li>
Participate in project post implementation reviews and contribute to recommendation reports in order to identify successful/unsuccessful project elements.</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>What You Need</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Drupal 6 and 7 proficiency, with enterprise-level development experience using Drupal 7. Drupal 8 familiarity; participation a plus. Three years of experience with Drupal is strongly preferred, meaning that you have more than a passing knowledge of Drupal 7. You know that, in most cases, there&#39;s a module for that. And you can find them and evaluate which of them is best suited for the client given the site&#39;s size, traffic, expected response, hardware cost, and other trade-offs.</li>
<li>
Expertise in standards-compliant, mobile-first responsive development, HTML5, jQuery, JavaScript itself, and CSS. Comfortable with Git, Drush and PHP. Firm understanding of Progressive Enhancement and Graceful Degradation. Experience with various front-end frameworks, cross-browser debugging, CSS preprocessors. Additional software expertise (e.g., HTML5 APIs, Twig, SASS, JSON, AJAX) a plus.</li>
<li>
Knowledge of accessibility (Section 508, WCAG) and usability best practices and techniques, Microdata, RDFa, WAI-ARIA, Schema.org.</li>
<li>
A demonstrable record of participation in the Drupal community (i.e., your Drupal.org ID shows a history of engagement and participation). You know your way around the Drupal.org issue queue and API documentation.</li>
<li>
Experience and comfort with Agile.</li>
<li>
Stay abreast of advances in user interface (both technical and experiential) and look for ways to appropriately integrate these advances into client websites.</li>
<li>
Bachelor&#39;s and/or post-graduate degree in Interaction Design, HCI, Information Systems, Computer Science, Software Engineering &ndash; or experience and expertise that demonstrate how that degree wasn&#39;t necessary. (Design maturity, analytical skills, problem solving ability, software engineering know-how.)</li>
<li>
Availability during North American business hours. Collaboration and communication require a degree of synchronous work, so we need some overlap. (Scrums are mid-morning EDT/EST via Skype. Asynchronous chats and ad hoc confabs occur as needed through the day.)</li>
<li>
Excellent communication skills. English is a must. Multilingual is a plus.</li>
<li>
You grok open source.</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>Who We Are</strong></p>
<p>
We are a compulsively creative studio planning, designing and building complex enterprise web applications. We demand a lot from ourselves and rely upon each other. We believe in open source and live and breathe Drupal. We are constantly searching for and implementing the best of best practices. We go above and beyond the call of duty and passionately find ways to surmount barriers.</p>
<p>
We value one another. We value teamwork. We go above and beyond the call of duty and passionately find ways to surmount barriers. We respect penetrating insight into client&rsquo;s business and technical problems and come up with effective solutions. We think on our feet and communicate effectively through written, verbal and visual channels. We have a reputation for sticking with it when the technical challenges get tough.<br />
We remember our roots and contribute back to the open source community. We are here to plant shade trees under which we shall never sit. We strive to empower you. Your success is our success.<br />
If this is you and you want to make an impact on our fast-growing company, love working in small, high performance teams and have the Drupal chops, we want to meet you.</p>
<p>
<strong>Why You&rsquo;ll Want to Work With Us</strong></p>
<p>
You can be part of a world-class team of Drupal developers with deep experience and a collegial, supportive team. You can get paid to give back to the Drupal community, and have the chance to be constantly exposed to new technologies and encouraged to implement them. We&rsquo;re a privately owned company with a very flat structure and an open door culture. And we believe in top tier compensation for top tier producers.</p>
<p>
<strong>NO THIRD-PARTY APPLICATIONS</strong></p>
<p>
Expand your career by working with a leader in Drupal development services. To learn more about Pingv visit <a href="http://www.pingv.com" target="_blank">www.pingv.com</a>.</p>
