<strong>Location: Boulder/Denver; Telecommuting for the ideal candidate</strong></p>
<p>
Pingv has an immediate opening for a high-energy Enterprise Drupal Account Executive with a proven track record in closing sales with enterprise-level Drupal clients. This is a high-visibility position reporting directly to the COO. It is commission-based with no earnings cap. It requires a thorough understanding of the Drupal CMS. With the help of the founders and backed by our top-tier technical team, you will take direct charge of Pingv&#39;s sales function.</p>
<p>
<strong>NO THIRD-PARTY APPLICATIONS. NO OUTSOURCERS. NO AGENCIES.</strong></p>
<p>
<strong>What You&#39;ll Do</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Leverage existing sales leads and identify sales leads of your own.</li>
<li>
Review requests for proposals (RFPs) to qualify potential clients.</li>
<li>
Draft and submit proposals.</li>
<li>
Make presentations to line and senior managers at Pingv and the prospects.</li>
<li>
Negotiate contracts and provide all follow-up to deliver signed contracts.</li>
<li>
Achieve sales targets by managing and closing complex sales cycles to C-level executives.</li>
<li>
Develop strong relationships to build stakeholder confidence backed by delivering commercial business solutions that exceed client expectations.</li>
<li>
Manage Pingv client relationships and make sure the client is happy post-launch.</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>What You Need</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
A thorough understanding of Drupal or other content management system (CMS) and how it solves client problems (absolutely required).</li>
<li>
Successful business development experience at C-level.</li>
<li>
Respect, trust and credibility in all your business dealings.</li>
<li>
A work ethic where you focus on creating value for your clients first.</li>
<li>
An established track record of developing new business opportunities by identifying, qualifying and closing top-tier corporate and/or government accounts while always utilizing a consultative sales process to align solutions to clients&rsquo; needs.</li>
<li>
Proven sales experience dealing with C-level and senior management in the corporate and/or government sectors.</li>
<li>
Demonstrated ability to navigate through an enterprise organization at senior executive and CXO levels.</li>
<li>
The ability to identify decision makers in a complex enterprise sale with multiple stakeholders.</li>
<li>
An existing network of strong business relationships within the U.S. market from which to create opportunities.</li>
<li>
A structured approach to selling, leveraging techniques such as solution selling.</li>
<li>
Excellent communication, interpersonal and proposal writing skills.</li>
<li>
Self-motivated and enthusiastic about reaching your targets in life and work.</li>
<li>
Driven by your own goals and financial successes.</li>
<li>
Clearly defined personal goals.</li>
<li>
Self-motivated, passionate and trustworthy.</li>
<li>
Bachelor&rsquo;s degree or in computer science, math, engineering, related discipline or an MBA.</li>
<li>
Ability to travel up to 20%.</li>
</ul>
<p>
