			<description><![CDATA[<p>
Pingv has an immediate opening for an experienced Drupal Senior Developer (SD) with a proven track record demonstrating mastery of Drupal architecture, design and code. The SD will apply Drupal sites and applications for Pingv&#39;s enterprise-level clients.</p>
<p>
We are looking for that smart, self-directed person with the right mix of passion for using Drupal-focused technology to solve problems, hands-on coding, mentoring others, talking to users, and contributing back to the open source community.</p>
<p>
At Pingv, we are building a great company filled with exceptional people who challenge and respect each other. Is this you?</p>
<p>
<strong>What You&#39;ll Do</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Become a key player on a variety of enterprise-level projects for a series of world-class clients.&nbsp; (We just launched Dwell Magazine site.)</li>
<li>
Build and configure Drupal websites.</li>
<li>
Work virtually, but not alone: you will be able to collaborate with our top-tier team on technical architecture, development, and other considerations, through project-focused Skype chat rooms. Voice-to-voice is ok, too.</li>
<li>
Communicate by voice on weekday morning during all-team Scrums.</li>
<li>
Participate and engage with the Drupal communities through our Drupal give program.</li>
<li>
Custom Drupal development following best practices in Drupal module development, jQuery, custom JavaScript.</li>
<li>
Third-party integrations; working with third-party APIs.</li>
<li>
Upgrade, patch, and contribute bug fixes to existing Drupal modules.</li>
<li>
Participate in project post implementation reviews and contribute to recommendation reports in order to identify successful/unsuccessful project elements.</li>
<li>
Help write case studies.</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>What You Need</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
You need to be mature and self-directed in order to stay focused while working in (your) virtual office.</li>
<li>
You grok open source.</li>
<li>
You&#39;re naturally curious and stay abreast of advances in web application technologies.</li>
<li>
A demonstrable record of participation in the Drupal community(i.e., your Drupal ID shows a history of engagement and participation, or equivalent).</li>
<li>
Professionalism, reliability, integrity. Ability to meet deadlines.</li>
<li>
Collaborative but can &quot;own&quot; a piece of a project and run with it.</li>
<li>
Expert in Drupal 7. Several years of enterprise-level experience with Drupal is strongly preferred, including knowledge of earlier versions of Drupal. You know your way around the Drupal.org issue queue and API documentation.</li>
<li>
You know that, in most cases, &quot;there&#39;s a module for that.&quot; And you can find them and evaluate which of them is best suited for the client given the site&#39;s size, traffic, expected response, hardware cost, and other trade-offs.</li>
<li>
Expert in PHP, MySQL, xhtml, HTML5. Expertise in standards-compliant, mobile-first responsive development, PHP, *SQL, Git, Drush. Firm understanding of Progressive Enhancement and Graceful Degradation. Experience with various development frameworks. Expertise/experience in alternative databases, Varnish, Solr/Lucene, Ngnix, HTML5 APIs, Twig, Node.js, JSON, AJAX a plus.</li>
<li>
Knowledge of metadata protocols (Microdata, RDFa, WAI-ARIA, Schema.org, Twitter cards).</li>
<li>
Experience and comfort with Agile.</li>
<li>
Availability during North American business hours. Collaboration and communication require a degree of synchronous work, so we need some overlap. (Scrums are mid-morning EDT/EST via Skype. Asynchronous chats and ad hoc confabs occur as needed through the day.)</li>
<li>
Bachelor&#39;s and/or post-graduate degree in Computer Science, Software Engineering, HCI, Information Systems ... or experience and expertise that demonstrate how that degree wasn&#39;t necessary. (Analytical skills, problem solving ability, software engineering know-how.)</li>
<li>
Excellent communication skills. Conversational English is a must. Multilingual is a plus.</li>
<li>
Drupal 8 familiarity; participation a plus.</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>Who We Are</strong></p>
<p>
We are a compulsively creative studio planning, designing and building some of the most complex Drupal-based enterprise web applications. We are constantly searching for and implementing the best of best practices. We demand a lot from ourselves and rely upon each other.</p>
<p>
We believe in open source and live and breathe Drupal. We remember our roots. We contribute back to the open source community.</p>
<p>
We value teamwork. We respect your insights. We strive to empower you. Your success is our success.</p>
<p>
We go above and beyond to surmount barriers. We think on our feet and communicate through written, verbal and visual channels.</p>
<p>
If you want to make an impact on our fast-growing company, love working in small, high performance teams and have the Drupal chops, we want to meet you.</p>
<p>
And we believe in top tier compensation for top tier producers.</p>
<p>
<strong>NO THIRD-PARTY APPLICATIONS</strong></p>
<p>
Expand your career by working with a leader in Drupal development services. To learn more about Pingv visit <a href="http://pingv.com">www.pingv.com</a>.</p>
